sections.code:
// store.js
import { store } from "olum";
export const cart = store({
  items: [],
  add(name) { this.items.push(name); },   // method shorthand — `this` is the store
  clear() { this.items = []; },
});

<!-- Basket.html -->
<script>
  import { cart } from "./store";
</script>
<p>{cart.items.length} items</p>          <!-- reading this subscribes Basket -->
<button onclick="cart.clear()">Empty</button>

sections.body:
OlumJS has no naked braces and one way to do each thing. The patterns you might reach for from other frameworks don't work here:

- Values for when / each / on* live inside the quotes — write when="x", not when={x}
- Bind inputs with value="{state.x}" plus an oninput handler — there's no model
- No prop shorthand or naked-brace props — write a="{a}", not {a} or a={a}
- Inline styles are a string with {expr}: style="color:{x}" — not :style
- Components are PascalCase — <Comp/>, not <comp/>
- Any {…} in text is interpolation — for a literal brace use {String.fromCharCode(123)}
- No event modifiers — call e.preventDefault() in the handler
- Reassigning state.list = state.list is a no-op — assign a fresh array (spread/map/filter) to force a re-render
- Arrow functions in a store lose this — use method shorthand: add() { this.items.push(x) }
- No <component is="..."> — switch components with an if / else-if / else chain over a string in state
- Key a crossfade off a primitive id (state.selectedId), not an object — deep reactivity breaks object-identity checks
